{title: Joy to the World}
{subtitle: Isaac Watts, 1719 — "Antioch" tune by Lowell Mason}
{key: D}
{time: 4/4}
{tempo: 96}
{comment: Pair with たみみなよろこべ (Japanese translation, 1922) and もろびとこぞりて (Japanese, 1923, sung to the same Antioch tune).}

{start_of_verse: 1}
[D]Joy to the [A]world; the [D]Lord is [A]come!
[Bm]Let Earth re[F#m]ceive her [G]King;
[D]Let every [A]heart pre[D]pare Him [A]room
[Bm]And heaven [F#m]and nature [G]sing[A]
[D]And heaven, and [G]nature [D]sing
[G]And heaven, and [A]heaven, and [D]nature sing.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
[D]Joy to the [A]Earth, the [D]Saviour [A]reigns!
[Bm]Let men their [F#m]songs em[G]ploy;
[D]While fields and [A]floods, rocks, [D]hills and [A]plains
[Bm]Repeat the [F#m]sounding [G]joy[A]
[D]Repeat the [G]sounding [D]joy
[G]Repeat, re[A]peat the [D]sounding joy.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 3}
[D]No more let [A]sins and [D]sorrows [A]grow
[Bm]Nor thorns in[F#m]fest the [G]ground;
[D]He comes to [A]make His [D]blessings [A]flow
[Bm]Far as the [F#m]curse is [G]found[A]
[D]Far as the [G]curse is [D]found
[G]Far as, far [A]as the [D]curse is found.
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 4}
[D]He rules the [A]world with [D]truth and [A]grace
[Bm]And makes the [F#m]nations [G]prove
[D]The glories [A]of His [D]righteous[A]ness
[Bm]And wonders [F#m]of His [G]love[A]
[D]And wonders [G]of His [D]love
[G]And wonders, [A]wonders [D]of His love.
{end_of_verse}
